name: Body Bizarre
overview: Criss-crossing the globe, "Body Bizarre" embarks on a voyage of discovery unlike any other. From India's child snake charmers to the world's hairiest girl, this series uncovers the real human stories behind the headlines. With deeply personal interviews and footage from the most unusual of day-to-day routines, it's an adventure through the truly astonishing.

seasons.name: Season 4
seasons.overview: The fourth series features nearly 50 new stories of medical anomalies and the people who are defying the odds against these rare medical situations. From Bangladesh to Madagascar to Brazil, these unique stories span more than 20 different countries.

episodes.name: The World's Thinnest Woman
episodes.overview: Hear the inspiring story of the world’s thinnest woman, Lizzie Velasquez, who has a disorder that stops her body from storing fat. Plus, follow more incredible human stories.

episodes.name: Elephant Man
episodes.overview: Hear the inspiring story of Lalit Ram, who has learned to live with a large benign tumour that has disfigured his face. Plus, follow more incredible human stories.

episodes.name: Born with an Extra Body
episodes.overview: Meet the 17-year-old girl who has learned to live with a very rare condition: a parasitic twin, and follow her journey to remove it. Plus, follow the story of Indonesia’s tree-man.

episodes.name: Unlock My Skull
episodes.overview: Meet Bobby Jo and two of her children who were all born suffering from Crouzon syndrome, and learn how they have come to terms with it. Plus, follow more incredible human stories.

episodes.name: Crying Blood
episodes.overview: Meet Delfina and hear her story, which involves a bizarre condition where she unexpectedly cries tears of blood. Plus, follow more incredible human stories.

episodes.name: Bubble Man
episodes.overview: Meet the man who suffers from a devastatingly disfiguring disorder, in which his body is covered in benign tumours. Plus, follow more incredible human stories.

episodes.name: Face-Eating Tumour
episodes.overview: In Brazil, a man has an upside-down head; triplets undergo a second round of life-saving surgeries and an Argentinian has giant-sized limbs.

episodes.name: Born With Two Heads
episodes.overview: A Puerto Rican boy’s face is melting away. In Afghanistan, doctors operate on a baby born with a parasitic tumour. A Brazilian girl’s feet won’t stop growing. In Sweden, a village can’t feel pain, and the man who lost his face to cancer finds a new look.

episodes.name: Joined at the Waist
episodes.overview: A girl has a terminal neck tumour, and one woman has a black and white body and the other has the world's largest hands.

episodes.name: Frozen by Fear
episodes.overview: A British man is literally scared stiff. A Thai man would be the tallest man in the word if he could stand. A child born with an unknown condition baffles the medical community.  A toddler covered in hair, and the man with an elephant leg.

episodes.name: Born with Three Legs
episodes.overview: A woman embraces a condition that causes her to grow facial hair and a Nepalese man born with three legs gets a life-changing operation.

episodes.name: My New Face
episodes.overview: A teen with a transgender girlfriend begins his sex-change transition and a Chinese woman lives with backwards hands and feet.

episodes.name: 50 Orgasms a Day
episodes.overview: An American woman has over 50 orgasms a day. Plus, a young, soccer prodigy from Brazil who was born without feet tackles a new sport.

episodes.name: Frozen Sisters
episodes.overview: In Nepal, four sisters have a condition that restricts movement, a man’s chin won’t stop growing and Chinese girl born with hair all over her body seeks treatment.

episodes.name: Bubble Man Meets the Pope
episodes.overview: The Pope blesses a badly disfigured man, a girl is born without arms and legs and a family has the world's longest hair.

episodes.name: World's Tallest Couple
episodes.overview: In Nepal, a 16in elder campaigns for the record of smallest man. A 200lb stomach tumour rolls out of a man. The world’s tallest couple worries about their children’s height. A black and white Brazilian family is bullied and the elephant man gets married.

episodes.name: I Cry Crystals
episodes.overview: Meet a teen who has aged prematurely, a schoolteacher who cries crystals, a mother with very brittle bones, and a boy with butterfly skin.

episodes.name: My 150lbs Tumour
episodes.overview: Meet a Frenchman with a rare shaking condition, and an American woman with an enormous stomach tumour, and the wibbly wobbly man.

episodes.name: Living Without Arms
episodes.overview: A Brazilian village fears the sun, a South African woman has giant legs, there's an armless American mother and a girl's tongue won't stop growing.

episodes.name: My Baby Has Two Heads
episodes.overview: Doctors operate on a huge neck tumour, an English teen is diagnosed with a rare aging condition, and an Indian baby is born with an extra head.

episodes.name: Boy with a Tail
episodes.overview: Meet an eight foot tall teen, a boy from India who possesses his own tail, a Brazilian man with supersized muscles, and the lobster woman.

episodes.name: Conjoined Twins Special
episodes.overview: Brazilian conjoined twins who share vital organs face risky separation surgery. In India, 12-year-old boys joined at the waist are inseparable.

episodes.name: Full Face Transplant
episodes.overview: A Polish woman undergoes a face transplant. A boy in China has a giraffe neck. A young Filipino girl has a sealed mouth.

episodes.name: Half Body Teen
episodes.overview: Chinese woman battles an aging condition, three Filipino brothers can never grow, Brazil has an all-dwarf soccer team, and a teen has half a body.

episodes.name: Living Statue
episodes.overview: Join a courageous girl who had acid thrown in her face, the lady known as the living statue, a no-limbed rapper, and a girl with huge tongue.

episodes.name: Girl with a Split Face
episodes.overview: A girl is born without a proper facial structure, a baby with an alien-shaped head, a four year old who weighs 66kg, and a legless gymnast.

episodes.name: A Tiger Ate My Face
episodes.overview: Hashmot Ali was fishing to feed his growing family in Bangladesh when a tiger attacked him, tearing his face away. Now, 20 years on, he seeks an operation to restore his features.

episodes.name: Ants in My Head
episodes.overview: 12-year-old Shreya Darji from India suffers an infestation where over a thousand ants were removed from her ears, with ten emerging every day. What causes this nightmarish problem?

episodes.name: My Face Is Killing Me
episodes.overview: 17-year old Moroccan teenager Zoubair lives with extreme facial tumours that cause difficulties with breathing. Doctors must perform complex, yet life-changing surgeries.

episodes.name: Limbless Little Girl
episodes.overview: Harmonie-Rose Allen contracted septicaemia as a baby, and had all her limbs amputated. Now her life is set to change as she gets prosthetics fitted. This is her amazing story.

episodes.name: My Giant Genitals
episodes.overview: Kenyan orphan Forence Owitni, 28, suffered a growth on his genitals that has swollen his testicles and penis to the size of bagpipes. Can doctors successfully operate on him?

episodes.name: Bubble Woman
episodes.overview: A look at how Sandra dos Santos, 50, from Rio, Brazil, lives the Rio beach lifestyle, despite the thousands of tiny tumours that bubble her skin - for which there is no cure.

episodes.name: Born with No Eyes
episodes.overview: A look at the life of four-year-old Brazilian boy Otavio Pimental, who was born entirely without eyes, as he embarks on a journey to be fitted with hand-crafted prosthetic eyes.

episodes.name: My Parasitic Twin
episodes.overview: In India, Hemlata Singh, gave birth to a boy with the head and arms of his dead twin attached to his chest. Can doctors save the newborn and separate him from his sibling's body?

episodes.name: My Baby's Face Tumour
episodes.overview: Just after 16-month-old Makaila was born, Doctors found a tumour on her face that threatened to choke and kill her. Now, her parents have found a surgeon to try and remove it.

episodes.name: Worlds Tiniest Brothers
episodes.overview: Claimed to be the world's smallest teenage brothers, Jobdan and Yuki Lizarme from Peru are the size of pre-schoolers, but are young men, aged 18 and 16. What stopped them growing?

episodes.overview: A boy born with no eyes. A separated conjoined twin adjusts to life after losing his twin brother. Two brothers suffer from a very rare bone condition. A boy living with a huge facial growth finally gets a diagnosis.

episodes.name: My Son Won't Grow
episodes.overview: The world's tiniest brothers find out if they'll ever be able to grow. Conjoined twins seek separation surgery. A boy with rare brain tumor. A girl living with a face tumor embraces her condition.

episodes.name: My Hand Belongs to a Dead Man
episodes.overview: The world's tallest child can't stop growing. A man learns to use a dead man's hand. A teenager discovers he has a parasitic twin and it's been growing inside him. A limbless girl gets fitted for prosthetic limbs.

episodes.name: My Body is Eating my Bones

episodes.name: Dad With No Limbs
episodes.overview: Three-year-old Ana suffers from a brain crushing prematurely fused skull. Alex had septicaemia that rapidly led to the amputation of all four of his limbs.

episodes.name: The Teen who wants a voice
episodes.overview: Rebecca vomits up to 12 times an hour and is often hospitalised. Jacque has a lymphatic malformation in her face that means she has never talked.

episodes.name: Boy with no Jaw
episodes.overview: Darina was born with a genetic disorder that's left her with a deformed mouth and jaw. Isaiah was born with his organs back to front and no jaw at all.

episodes.name: Allergic to light
episodes.overview: Fatima is allergic to light and even indoors must take precautions to avoid succumbing to skin cancer. Amar's face has been destroyed by a bony tumour.

episodes.name: Boy with no eyes
episodes.overview: Mahesh weighs 150kg, twice the weight of an average man, due to a syndrome that encourages constant eating. A development in the womb left Christian with no eyes.

episodes.name: The Boy who's eyes fall out
episodes.overview: Sulaiman suffers from Cruzon syndrome, which causes his eye to fall from his skull. Tony became a hermit when huge lumps grew around his face.

episodes.name: Balloon man
episodes.overview: In Peru, diver Alejandro's body has blown up like a balloon. Marc from Germany has to drink 20 litres of water every day or risks death.

episodes.name: Joined at the Head
episodes.overview: Italian professor Letitzia feels no physical pain and has broken limbs with no discomfort. Filipino twins Czarina and Ciara, 7, were born joined at the head.

episodes.name: Heart on the outside
episodes.overview: In India, Arpit was born with his heart positioned on the outside of his rib cage. In Brazil, Winny suffers from a rare disorder that means her skin falls off.

episodes.name: My New Face
episodes.overview: In Mexico, Adrian, 22, has a basketball-sized tumour on the side of his face. In the US Janice has a giant leg that has grown out of proportion to the...

episodes.name: Little Dany's First Smile
episodes.overview: In Mexico Dany, 8, was born with Moebius Syndrome which paralysed her face. She's set to undergo delicate microsurgery. Will she smile for the first time?

episodes.name: My Body Is Eating Itself
episodes.overview: Lee, 42, from England, has a rare stomach disorder that means his body is eating itself. In Columbia, Edward is just 70cm tall. Can a specialist explain it?

episodes.name: World's Fattest Baby
episodes.overview: In India, baby Chahat weighs as much a six-year-old. Her family travel 2000kms to see a top obesity expert. In Spain, Juana is allergic to the outside world.

episodes.overview: When Richard, 43, was shot in the face he underwent a face transplant, but now has complications. In a Peruvian village boys and men are going blind.

episodes.name: My Child's Huge Hands
episodes.overview: American toddler Cora was born with a condition causing her hands to swell up. In Brazil, Judite, was born with deformed legs and spine and walks on all fours.

episodes.name: My Dwarf Baby
episodes.overview: The UK's shortest married couple both have dwarfism and are expecting their second child. In India, Miria is three and has a severe cleft palate.

episodes.name: Born Joined At The Head
episodes.overview: Brazilian toddlers Ysabelle and Ysadora were born joined at the head. In Mexico Flor, 19, has a rare disorder causing half her face to sink in on itself.
